cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with sequence-to-sequence models used in natural language processing tasks such as machine translation and summarization. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new algorithm for optimizing sequence-to-sequence models. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with learning algorithms and cs.CV (Computer Vision) as it mentions experiments conducted on image captioning. Finally, it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it uses recurrent neural networks to approximate the latent distributions.
